  type="Article"
>
  <article aria-labelledby="grievance-grifter-title">
    <h1 id="grievance-grifter-title">Grievance Grifter™</h1>
    <h2>The Complete Reaction-in-a-Box Movement Starter Kit</h2>

    <blockquote>
      <p>“For the man who has discovered that society is complicated, but a microphone, a villain, and a payment funnel make it beautifully simple.”</p>
    </blockquote>

    <p><strong>This is not politics.</strong><br />
      <strong>This is not philosophy.</strong><br />
      <strong>This is not public service.</strong></p>
    <p class="site-intro">This is the eternal conference-room pitch, updated for the culture war.</p>

    <section aria-labelledby="core-promise">
      <h2 id="core-promise">The Core Promise</h2>
      <p>Do you feel that vague national decline could be converted into:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>a mailing list,</li>
        <li>a paid community,</li>
        <li>a speaking career,</li>
        <li>a conference circuit,</li>
        <li>a merch shop,</li>
        <li>a book deal,</li>
        <li>a livestream audience,</li>
        <li>and a leadership role in a movement you did not actually build?</li>
      </ul>
      <p><strong>Then welcome to Grievance Grifter™.</strong><br />Where real pain becomes recurring revenue.</p>
    </section>

    <section aria-labelledby="product-ladder">
      <h2 id="product-ladder">The Product Ladder</h2>

      <section aria-labelledby="free-webinar">
        <h3 id="free-webinar">Level 1: The Free Webinar</h3>
        <p><strong>“Something Is Wrong — And You Were Right to Notice”</strong></p>
        <p>A 90-minute emotional induction for people who are not stupid, not imaginary, and not wrong to feel abandoned.</p>
        <p>The trick is simple: validate the pain, then quietly redirect it toward your chosen enemy.</p>
        <p><strong>Not:</strong></p>
        <p>“Your town has been damaged by 40 years of underinvestment, financialisation, policy failure, social atomisation and state decay.”</p>
        <p><em>Too complicated.</em></p>
        <p><strong>Instead:</strong></p>
        <p class="site-intro">“They did this to you.”</p>
        <p><strong>Much better. Cleaner. More clickable.</strong></p>
      </section>

      <section aria-labelledby="starter-pack">
        <h3 id="starter-pack">Level 2: The Starter Pack</h3>
        <p><strong>“From Concerned Citizen to Movement Builder in 30 Days”</strong></p>
        <p><strong>Includes:</strong></p>
        <ul>
          <li>The laminated Enemy Map.</li>
          <li>The “I’m Just Asking Questions” phrasebook.</li>
          <li>The Pub Bloke Authenticity Checklist.</li>
          <li>The “I’m Being Silenced” content calendar.</li>
          <li>The “Ordinary People Are Sick of It” caption bank.</li>
          <li>The “Mainstream Media Won’t Tell You This” email template.</li>
          <li>Three starter villains and one emergency backup villain.</li>
        </ul>
        <p><strong>Bonus cassette, now updated to podcast format:</strong><br />Tape of the Week: <em>How to Sound Brave While Punching Down.</em></p>
      </section>

      <section aria-labelledby="core-course">
        <h3 id="core-course">Level 3: The Core Course</h3>
        <p><strong>The Conference Room to Culture War Pipeline</strong></p>
        <dl>
          <dt><strong>Module 1: Pain Harvesting for Beginners</strong></dt>
          <dd>Learn how to identify real distress without ever committing to a workable solution.</dd>
          <dt><strong>Module 2: Enemy Compression</strong></dt>
          <dd>Take a vast, multi-causal social problem and compress it into one emotionally available target.</dd>
          <dt><strong>Module 3: The Everyman Costume</strong></dt>
          <dd>How to look like “one of the lads” while operating a media machine, donor pipeline, and personal brand ecosystem.</dd>
        </dl>
      </section>
    </section>
  </article>

